[~sjones], I have a policy where a limit has been set to zero.
Error in uploaded policy: {"Version": "2011-04-01", "Statement": [{"Action": "iam:CreateInstanceProfile", "Resource": "*", "Effect": "Limit", "Condition": {"NumericLessThanEquals": {"iam:quota-instanceprofilenumber": "8"}}}, {"Action": "iam:CreateGroup", "Resource": "*", "Effect": "Limit", "Condition": {"NumericLessThanEquals": {"iam:quota-groupnumber": "8"}}}, {"Action": "iam:CreateUser", "Resource": "*", "Effect": "Limit", "Condition": {"NumericLessThanEquals": {"iam:quota-usernumber": "8"}}}, {"Action": "iam:CreateRole", "Resource": "*", "Effect": "Limit", "Condition": {"NumericLessThanEquals": {"iam:quota-rolenumber": "0"}}}]}

If the value is above zero, I don't get an error. If it changed to zero, I get this error. In this case, it's the iam:quota-rolenumber. Does this mean that I must remove conditions of value zero? I find that does work, but I'd like confirmation as a sanity check.
